metadata.name: Dencity #724
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: V.Mountains #79
metadata.description:
V.Mountains is an abstract representation of the turbulence and chaos of our life.



The mountain is a symbol of the way that life is constantly in flux,

of the way that we are constantly trying to make sense of the world around us.



The mountain is a source of inspiration, a place of refuge, a source of strength.

It is a place where we can go to reflect on our lives, to find peace and solace.



The mountain is a symbol of hope.

It is a reminder that, no matter how dark and cold the world may be, there is always a chance for new beginnings.



The mountain is a symbol of the human spirit, and of our ability to persevere in the face of adversity.

It is a representation of our journey through life, with all of its ups and downs.

It is a reminder that, no matter how difficult the path may be,
we can always reach the summit if we are willing to put in the hard work.



Created in Vanilla Javascript.


S - to download image.


Libraries used:

noise.js by Joseph Gentle.
Javascript-Voronoi by Raymond Hill.

metadata.name: Hauntological Herbarium #35
metadata.description:
Idea of Hauntology is referring to the return or persistence of elements from the social or cultural past, as in the manner of a ghost.

This implies a contemporary culture's persistent recycling of retro aesthetics and a sense of nostalgia for the lost futures.

Flowers and herbaceous plants are short-lived creatures, but when dried, in herbarium mode, they can be stored much longer and ensure the repetition of the stories associated with them.
Therefore, special conditions must be created for the existence of ghosts. These conditions are usually created by people, and sometimes people themselves become these very conditions.

Artwork is based on PNG layers (with masks), Disco Diffusion, python and p5.js code.

metadata.name: Mornings #1
metadata.description:
... a photograph taken at morning on a film camera somewhere in the American Midwest. The sun is present enough to light the sky, but still remains below the horizon leaving the land slightly underexposed and the trees nearly silhouetted ...

---

My journey continues to make the most compelling landscapes I can spring from a text editor. I spent a lot of time examining painted as well as traditional digital art landscapes, both of which are incredibly mature mediums. Paint, in particular, seems to be completely mastered - with some artist's work leaving nothing to be desired. What I have seen in digital has also blown me away. I want to work towards the bar set by these artists and marry their aesthetic prowess with the power, variety, and excitement of generative art.

--

// Technical Notes
-The render will take ~2-3 minutes.

-Default resolution is 3000x6000 px (including letterbox). While it's possible to render at any resolution, this is my intended resolution for the project - the product of an artistic choice to make the piece behave more like a photograph. This limited (but still high) resolution gives the features at the smallest scales some fuzziness, giving a sense that detail extends below the resolution of the piece. I think this imparts a more natural aesthetic as opposed to the perfect forms and edges of canvas shapes.


// Controls
Press "z" to zoom in, and take a look around. Keys "1", "2", "3", and "4" to control the zoom amount.

Press "s" to download the image. Right-click-save will not work.


// Owners
Token owners will have access to artist prints. Send me a DM on twitter.

metadata.name: tratti #229
metadata.description:
"tratti" is an Italian word that has many different meanings. When we started working on this piece, we wanted to create something that combines our traits ("tratti" in Italian).
We had this urge to channel the turbulent times we're living in now into this artwork using just lines ("tratti" in Italian).

We don't know what to do now, we're here, and that's all that matters. We're here for our families, our friends, and our community. Like everything in life, there are joyful times and challenging times. We must accept happiness as something that is not constant but that we feel at times (a "tratti" in Italian).

With "tratti", we want to send a message to every disheartened human being: "Stay strong and never let anyone or anything crush the hope in you. Joyful times are around the corner".

----

metadata.name: Insula #62
metadata.description:
An audiovisual collection.
.
Click to start the sound.
..
Insula is an endless generative music player.
...
There are 6 different grid size; 4 squares and 20 squares are the rare ones.

2 different background texture; Lines, Grain.

2 different color placement; Circular, Linear.

7 different noise types.

8 different scales with fixed root notes; C Maj., C Lydian, D Dorian, D Min. Penta., G Maj., G Maj. Penta., F Mixolydian, F Min.

2 different rhythmical structures; 2:3, 4:5.

2 different note indicator style; Circle and Square. Square is rare and behaves differently.

5 different note indicator line divisions.
....
Harmonization process based on Avro Part's 'Tintinnabuli' style.

Grid design inspired from Novation's Launchpad.


Made with p5.js and Web Audio.

Ilgın İçözü, December 2021
@distcollective
